content.description: Climb up awesome edges and crimps till you can move right and top out.
content.location: Middle of the large boulder that forms the corridor.  Cliff side.

content.description: Start under a small roof either matched on an undercling or squeezing the block.  Move up the blocky section, out to a crimp, and mantle the topout
content.location: Moving through the corridor, this climb will be to your right as you exit.

content.description:
Climb the large boulder that lies at the start of Bagel and Locks. Under cling the crack and smear your way to the top. 

  Alternative start to Tarter Sauce, Start behind the boulder at the base of the problem and stem/layback the corner till you can gain the underclings.
content.protection: Crash Pad, single rack, TR (tree anchors and long slings or static line)
content.location: Just to the left and above Bagels and Locks

climbs.name: The Something Seam
climbs.fa: FA Mack Johnson and Andy Ward 1988

content.description: Climb the slab below the The Nothing Seam and finish up The Nothing Seam.
content.protection: single rack(small gear) TR(tree Anchors, long slings or static line)

content.description:
Start as if you were going to climb Tarter Sauce but step right on to the slab and climb the thin seam-crack. 

  Needs a cleaning
content.location: To the left of Tarter Sauce

content.protection: crash pad, single rack TR(tree anchors)
content.location: To the left of Numb Knees half way up the corridor

content.description: Start on the crack just left of Vector and just right of a birds nest.  Move up to a large hold and make a series of thin moves in horizontal seams to a balance top out on a great edge
content.location: In the corridor on the block.  Start at the end of the long low crack just right of a birds nest.

content.description:
Start on two small underclings for hands, a low ledge for feet. fire up to a thin rail, mantle, slap lip and small crystal, top out. 

  The start might be height dependent
content.location: This is the first problem you'll approach/see at The Left End. High ball boulder problem about 10' from the left side of the crag

content.description: Climb the obvious dirty chimney, passing a loose block.
content.protection: Crash Pad, single rack, TR(tree anchors)
content.location: To the left and up the hill from The Something Seam

content.description: Climb the obvious left leaning thin finger crack
content.protection: Crash pad, single rack or TR

content.description: This is the first crag you'll see and approach from the railroad bed. It's made up a long low wall about 12' at its lowest and 20' at its highest. On the left you'll find a large boulder about 8' from the main wall creating a small corridor. This boulder has a few undocumented boulder problems on it.
